name: DEWI RATIH
description: Dewi Ratih is a moon goddess in Javanese Hindu culture and Balinese mythology. It is also said that she is the goddess of beauty. The famous myth about the goddess Ratih is about a lunar eclipse. At the time of the eclipse, the goddess Ratih who was running in heaven was caught by Kala Rau. He was pursued because he was the one who told the god Vishnu that Kala Rau wanted to drink from Tirta Amertha (Water of eternal life).
